The paper discusses a privacy-preserving algorithm for machine learning, specifically for estimating parameters in generalized linear models using iteratively reweighted least squares (IRLS). This topic falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and privacy (cs.CR). The algorithm involves analyzing the sensitivity of each moment separately, which could also fall under information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of concentrated differential privacy formalism is a statistical method that could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
